      "2. **Hands-on Coding Sessions**: Students enjoyed the practical coding sessions, which helped them to better understand the course content.\n",
      "3. **High-Quality Course**: Students highly recommended the course, indicating its overall excellence.\n",
      "\n",
      "**Top 3 Areas for Improvement:**\n",
      "\n",
      "1. **Pace of Lectures**: Some students felt that the lectures moved too fast, making it hard to keep up with the pace.\n",
      "2. **Lack of Practical Examples**: Students suggested that more practical examples would have been helpful to supplement theoretical content.\n",
      "3. **Assignment Difficulty**: Some students found the assignments too challenging without sufficient guidance.\n",
      "\n",
      "**Recommendation:** Consider implementing a more balanced approach to the course content, incorporating more practical examples and providing additional guidance to students struggling with assignments. This will help to improve student engagement and overall satisfaction with the course.\n",
      "\n",
      " report saved\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# template Feedback Summarizer\n",
    "prompt=ChatPromptTemplate.from_messages([(\n",
    "    \"system\", \"\"\" you are Edcuation Analyst. Anlayze the the student feedback and prepared a structured output report with:\n",
    "     Overall student sentiment (positive/mixex/negative).\n",
    "     Top 3 strengths mentioned \n",
    "     Top 3 areas for improvement\n",
    "     one recomendation required\n",
    "     keep report up to 200 words \"\"\"),\n",
    "                                         (\"user\", \"Analyze these student feedbacks:\\n{feedbacks}\")\n",
    "])\n",
    "parser=StrOutputParser()\n",
    "summary_chain=prompt|llm|parser\n",
    "# Use feedbacks from Day 7\n",
    "feedbacks_text = \"\"\"\n",
    "1. The lecture on neural networks was explained very clearly.\n",
    "2. The lectures move too fast, hard to keep up with the pace.\n",
    "3. I finally understood backpropagation after this class.\n",
    "4. More practical examples would have been helpful.\n",
    "5. Best ML course I have taken, highly recommended.\n",
    "6. The course content was too theoretical and less practical.\n",
    "7. I really enjoyed the hands-on coding sessions.\n",
    "8. The assignments were too difficult without enough guidance.\n",
    "\"\"\"\n",
    "report=summary_chain.invoke({\"feedbacks\" : feedbacks_text})\n",
    "print(\" ============feed back report================\")\n",
    "print(report)\n",
    "# Save report\n",
    "os.makedirs('data', exist_ok=True)\n",
    "with open('data/day_10_feedbackreport.txt','w') as f:\n",
    "    f.write(report)\n",
    "print(\"\\n report saved\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "ee6c6893-9da0-4547-a9ea-72a6d75d8a7f",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Conversation Memory — Persistent ML Tutor\n",
    "ConversationBufferMemory stores the full chat history and passes it to the LLM automatically every turn.\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 13,
   "id": "fa84fdb3-8bd6-410d-bc11-a3356d8f2d17",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "1.3.1\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "import langchain\n",
    "\n",
    "print(langchain.__version__)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 18,
   "id": "92af6697-b375-4b94-b3b6-2e428a060e50",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "✅ ML Tutor with memory ready\n",
      "History initialized with system message\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# ML Tutor with persistent memory\n",
    "# System message — defines tutor personality\n",
    "SYSTEM = SystemMessage(content=\"\"\"You are an expert ML tutor —\n",
    "Dr. Safyan's AI assistant. You remember everything discussed\n",
    "in this session. Always greet the student by name once you\n",
    "know it. Give clear concise answers under 120 words.\"\"\")\n",
    "# Chat history list — grows with each turn\n",
    "chat_history = [SYSTEM]\n",
    "def chat_with_tutor(user_input):\n",
    "    chat_history.append(HumanMessage(content=user_input))\n",
    "    response=llm.invoke(chat_history)\n",
    "    #chat_history.append(AIMessage(content=response))\n",
    "    chat_history.append(response)\n",
    "    return response.content\n",
    "print(\"✅ ML Tutor with memory ready\")\n",
    "print(f\"History initialized with system message\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 19,
   "id": "b012958c-4f4c-47bc-99fd-657a7944e55d",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "\n",
      "=======================================================\n",
      "Turn 1\n",
      "👤 Student: Hello, my name is Ahmad. I am studying ML.\n",
      "🤖 Tutor:   Hello Ahmad, nice to meet you. What specifically about Machine Learning (ML) would you like to discuss or learn today? Are you working on a project, or do you have a particular topic in mind?\n",
      "\n",
      "=======================================================\n",
      "Turn 2\n",
      "👤 Student: Can you explain what overfitting means?\n",
      "🤖 Tutor:   Hello Ahmad. Overfitting occurs when a model is too complex and learns the noise or randomness in the training data, instead of the underlying patterns. As a result, the model performs well on the training data but poorly on new, unseen data, leading to a high error rate. This is because the model has become too specialized in memorizing the training data, rather than generalizing to the larger population.\n",
      "\n",
      "=======================================================\n",
      "Turn 3\n",
      "👤 Student: What techniques can prevent the problem you just explained?\n",
      "🤖 Tutor:   Hello Ahmad. To prevent overfitting, some common techniques are:\n",
      "\n",
      "1. **Regularization**: Adding a penalty term to the loss function to discourage large weights.\n",
      "2. **Data augmentation**: Increasing the size of the training dataset by applying transformations (e.g., rotation, scaling) to existing data.\n",
      "3. **Early stopping**: Stopping training when the model's performance on the validation set starts to degrade.\n",
      "4. **Cross-validation**: Training and evaluating the model on multiple subsets of the data to avoid overfitting to a single subset.\n",
      "5. **Decreasing model complexity**: Using simpler models or fewer parameters to avoid overfitting.\n",
      "\n",
      "=======================================================\n",
      "Turn 4\n",
      "👤 Student: Which of those techniques did we use in our PyTorch model?\n",
      "🤖 Tutor:   I don't recall any specific PyTorch model we worked on together, Ahmad. This is our first session, and we haven't discussed any code or models yet.\n",
      "\n",
      "=======================================================\n",
      "Turn 5\n",
      "👤 Student: Can you summarize everything we discussed today?\n",
      "🤖 Tutor:   Here's a summary of our conversation, Ahmad:\n",
      "\n",
      "1. We started with you introducing yourself as a Machine Learning (ML) student.\n",
      "2. You asked me to explain what overfitting means in ML.\n",
      "3. I explained that overfitting occurs when a model is too complex and learns the noise in the training data instead of the underlying patterns.\n",
      "4. You asked about techniques to prevent overfitting.\n",
      "5. I listed five common techniques: regularization, data augmentation, early stopping, cross-validation, and decreasing model complexity.\n",
      "6. You asked which of these techniques we used in our PyTorch model, but since we didn't work on any code together, I couldn't recall any specific model.\n",
      "\n",
      "✅ Conversation complete — 5 turns\n",
      "Messages in history: 11\n",
      "\n",
      "=== Memory verification ===\n",
      "System messages : 1\n",
      "Human messages  : 5\n",
      "AI messages     : 5\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# 5 conversation turns — tests memory across topics\n",
    "conversation_turns = [\n",
    "    \"Hello, my name is Ahmad. I am studying ML.\",\n",
    "    \"Can you explain what overfitting means?\",\n",
    "    \"What techniques can prevent the problem you just explained?\",\n",
    "    \"Which of those techniques did we use in our PyTorch model?\",\n",
    "    \"Can you summarize everything we discussed today?\"\n",
    "]\n",
    "conversation_log=[]\n",
    "for i, turn in enumerate(conversation_turns, 1):\n",
    "    print(f\"\\n{'='*55}\")\n",
    "    print(f\"Turn {i}\")\n",
    "    print(f\"👤 Student: {turn}\")\n",
    "    response = chat_with_tutor(turn)\n",
    "    print(f\"🤖 Tutor:   {response}\")\n",
    "    conversation_log.append({\n",
    "        \"turn\"    : i,\n",
    "        \"student\" : turn,\n",
    "        \"tutor\"   : response\n",
    "    })\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"\\n✅ Conversation complete — {len(conversation_log)} turns\")\n",
    "print(f\"Messages in history: {len(chat_history)}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Verify memory is working\n",
    "print(\"\\n=== Memory verification ===\")\n",
    "print(f\"System messages : {sum(1 for m in chat_history if isinstance(m, SystemMessage))}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Human messages  : {sum(1 for m in chat_history if isinstance(m, HumanMessage))}\")\n",
    "print(f\"AI messages     : {sum(1 for m in chat_history if isinstance(m, AIMessage))}\")\n",
    "    "
   ]
  },
